Philippine Stocks: Vista Land & Lifescapes, Aboitiz Power Corp.

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-03-14T04:49:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/philippine-stocks-vista-land-and-lifescapes-aboitiz-power.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.1 percent to
3,918.70, its lowest close since March 8.       Vista Land & Lifescapes, Inc. (VLL PM), a Philippine
builder, rose 0.7 percent to 2.77 pesos, the highest level since
Jan. 28. The company plans to spend more than 45 billion pesos
($1 billion) from 2011 to 2013 to “accelerate” the development
of four of the company’s projects, it said in a statement.        Aboitiz Power Corp. (AP)   climbed 2.8 percent to 30.30
pesos, its biggest advance since Feb. 28, after Philippine Star
reported today that the group may build a water reservoir and a
hydroelectric plant in the province of Isabela. The shares also
began trading today without the right to a dividend payout.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  